7
00:00:37,130 --> 00:00:39,870
When will she regain her consciousness?

8
00:00:39,870 --> 00:00:42,370
I cannot say for sure.

9
00:00:42,370 --> 00:00:47,250
She has a slight cerebral contusion due to the hit. However, surgery won't be necessary.

10
00:00:47,250 --> 00:00:51,230
As for now, all we can do is to wait.

11
00:00:51,230 --> 00:00:53,860
- Please, look after her.
- Yes, Ma'am.

12
00:00:53,860 --> 00:00:55,730
Please excuse me.

13
00:00:58,290 --> 00:01:00,030
According to the police report,

14
00:01:00,030 --> 00:01:03,770
she attempted to help a student who collapsed.

15
00:01:03,770 --> 00:01:06,280
That's when she was hit by a motorcycle.

16
00:01:06,770 --> 00:01:08,980
That's something she would do.

17
00:01:10,240 --> 00:01:12,220
Agreed.

18
00:01:13,850 --> 00:01:17,530
- I just finished my exam. How's Harumi?
- Well...

19
00:01:17,530 --> 00:01:22,610
her right leg is broken and she hit her head due to the impact.

20
00:01:22,610 --> 00:01:27,650
Her life isn't in danger, but she still remains unconscious.

21
00:01:27,650 --> 00:01:29,580
- What?
<i>- The hospital she's staying in is</i>

22
00:01:29,580 --> 00:01:34,210
<i>the Jonan General Hospital in the Bunkyo Ward. Her room is in the building B on the third floor-</i>

23
00:01:34,870 --> 00:01:37,240
It's Yakumo. Yuri,

24
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:40,590
there's nothing you can do, even if you come.

25
00:01:40,590 --> 00:01:44,190
<i>You still have exams tomorrow, right? Concentrate on that.</i>

26
00:01:44,190 --> 00:01:47,310
- But-
- Junko would say the same.

27
00:01:47,310 --> 00:01:51,590
Isn't that why you didn't come here instead of skipping the exam?

28
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,010
<i>Good luck.</i>

29
00:02:17,290 --> 00:02:22,000
<i>[The Second Exam for the University of Tokyo, Day 2]</i>

30
00:02:44,070 --> 00:02:45,720
Yes?

31
00:02:50,630 --> 00:02:54,600
Please, get some sleep. I'll take over.

32
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,460
Thank you.

33
00:03:06,990 --> 00:03:09,740
Junko, wake up!

34
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,740
Junko, can you hear me?

35
00:03:17,740 --> 00:03:19,310
Jun!

36
00:03:25,660 --> 00:03:27,830
I'm so relieved!

37
00:03:27,830 --> 00:03:29,550
Yuri-yuri...

38
00:03:30,450 --> 00:03:32,420
What happened to Yuri-yuri?

39
00:03:40,940 --> 00:03:41,960
Jun!

40
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:43,960
Masashi.

41
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:45,960
Jun...

42
00:03:47,210 --> 00:03:50,480
I'm relieved... I'm so relieved!

43
00:03:51,820 --> 00:03:55,180
Masashi, sorry to have you worried.

44
00:03:55,180 --> 00:04:00,260
Tell me about it. I thought you wouldn't wake up...

45
00:04:00,860 --> 00:04:05,410
When I was hit, I thought I was going to die.

46
00:04:05,410 --> 00:04:06,370
I hope not.

47
00:04:06,370 --> 00:04:12,050
Tell me. Did your life flashes before your eyes when you were about to die?

48
00:04:13,580 --> 00:04:16,040
I didn't.

49
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:20,650
Masashi, what about you? How was the reception?

50
00:04:22,820 --> 00:04:25,810
A success. A grand success at that.

51
00:04:25,810 --> 00:04:28,950
I'm so happy for you.

52
00:04:31,670 --> 00:04:32,830
Junko.

53
00:04:32,830 --> 00:04:33,600
Mom.

54
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:36,740
- Are you all right? Do you feel pain anywhere?
- I'm all right.

55
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:41,490
The doctor said, since she hit her head,

56
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:46,540
she'd have to be hospitalized for a while for tests and observation.

57
00:04:49,350 --> 00:04:55,010
Since I'll be bored, I should find a hobby.

58
00:04:59,910 --> 00:05:01,870
<i>[Jonan General Hospital]</i>

59
00:05:06,750 --> 00:05:10,810
<i>Making a choice means throwing something away.</i>

60
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:22,010
<i>Good work on your exams. Jun just regained consciousness.</i>

61
00:05:22,010 --> 00:05:24,210
<i>She's in good health, so no need to stress.</i>

62
00:05:24,210 --> 00:05:25,620
<i>[Masashi Yakumo]</i>

63
00:05:25,620 --> 00:05:27,210
Just now?

64
00:05:28,850 --> 00:05:31,120
<i>[Jonan General Hospital]</i>

65
00:05:46,190 --> 00:05:48,850
Kyohei.

66
00:05:48,850 --> 00:05:51,910
- Did you just get home? It's quite late.
- Yeah.

67
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:55,950
How was the test?

68
00:05:59,670 --> 00:06:01,850
I'm the same as you, Dad.

69
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:06,550
I'm the exact same.

70
00:06:06,550 --> 00:06:11,470
<i>if you're reaching for the top, there will the time when you have to make tough choices.</i>

71
00:06:11,470 --> 00:06:14,630
<i> I will always choose both.</i>

72
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:34,940
<i>[Kyohei Yuri]</i>

73
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:41,690
<i>At the moment I thought I was going to die, one thing came to my mind.</i>

74
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,680
<i>[Junko Harumi]</i>

75
00:06:48,230 --> 00:06:50,570
<i>It was...</i>

76
00:06:57,980 --> 00:06:59,940
Yuri Geller.
<i>(T/N: Uri Geller, an Israeli-British illusionist.)</i>

77
00:07:13,210 --> 00:07:17,180
<i>[A Story to Read When You First Fall in Love]</i>

78
00:07:17,180 --> 00:07:21,850
<i>[Finale]</i>

79
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:28,520
Why don't you give him a call?

80
00:07:31,090 --> 00:07:35,580
He's probably feeling guilty.

81
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:39,280
For taking the exam instead of visiting you.

82
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:44,170
He probably feels like he's abandoned you.

83
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:48,140
Junko.

84
00:07:48,970 --> 00:07:53,010
Yurihei likes you.

85
00:07:57,050 --> 00:08:02,410
But that was merely... bait I was giving him,

86
00:08:02,410 --> 00:08:05,980
during this short exam period.

87
00:08:05,980 --> 00:08:11,020
I don't mind if he wakes up from his dreams.

88
00:08:11,020 --> 00:08:16,010
- Junko, are you okay with that?
- Remember? Yuri-yuri is attending the University of Tokyo.

89
00:08:17,290 --> 00:08:20,940
I don't want to become a burden

90
00:08:20,940 --> 00:08:23,750
to his future.

91
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:28,580
<i>No riding skateboards in the hallways.</i>

92
00:08:33,670 --> 00:08:37,040
So now we wait for the results.

93
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:42,450
You self-graded your exam, right? What did Harumi say?

94
00:08:44,650 --> 00:08:46,420
I haven't seen her.

95
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:52,460
The morning of the first exams, she got into an accident and hospitalized.

96
00:08:52,460 --> 00:08:53,620
Say what?

97
00:08:53,620 --> 00:08:58,310
She's regained consciousness, and she stays there for observation.

98
00:08:58,310 --> 00:09:00,710
Why haven't you visited her?

99
00:09:02,970 --> 00:09:08,430
At the moment, I chose my exams over Harumi.

100
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:14,210
Harumi said before, choosing means eliminating the alternative.

101
00:09:14,210 --> 00:09:17,230
Maybe she thinks I eliminated her.

102
00:09:17,230 --> 00:09:18,670
Plus, she hasn't called me.

103
00:09:18,670 --> 00:09:20,670
That can't be true.

104
00:09:20,670 --> 00:09:24,280
I'm surprised you were able to concentrate on exams, given the circumstances.

105
00:09:26,710 --> 00:09:31,720
Since I chose my exams, I double-downed on concentrating.

106
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:35,750
I did my very best.

107
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:38,400
Do you have any regrets?

108
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,790
I don't regret on my decision.

109
00:09:41,450 --> 00:09:43,140
But...

110
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:47,300
I've come to hate myself.

111
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:56,600
<i>[Teito International Corporation]</i>

112
00:10:00,190 --> 00:10:04,320
Yakumo, what did the boss say?

113
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:09,540
I'll no longer go to Russia, and I've been taken off the project.

114
00:10:09,540 --> 00:10:10,950
What?

115
00:10:11,730 --> 00:10:14,610
Maybe I'll have to transfer to a different department.

116
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:18,100
With this,

117
00:10:18,790 --> 00:10:21,240
I have to say good-bye to you as well.

118
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:23,130
Yakumo...

119
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:30,240
Well, I'm fine. I have no regrets.

120
00:10:33,010 --> 00:10:38,000
So what was her reply to your proposal?

121
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:41,790
She hasn't responded yet.

122
00:10:41,790 --> 00:10:45,950
But considering my situation with Junko,

123
00:10:45,950 --> 00:10:49,110
maybe it's better that I'm not going to Russia.

124
00:10:49,110 --> 00:10:53,640
Now I can wait for her reply for months, or even years.

125
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:56,210
Are you serious?

126
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:02,480
I'm no longer miffed, I'm actually mad.

127
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:06,860
- Let's go tomorrow.
- Where?
- To see your cousin in the hospital.

128
00:11:06,860 --> 00:11:12,050
I'll accompany you there to assist your marriage.

129
00:11:12,050 --> 00:11:14,310
Thank you so much.

130
00:11:14,310 --> 00:11:15,640
<i>[Jonan General Hospital]</i>

131
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:18,280
We also have magazines on haiku poems,

132
00:11:18,280 --> 00:11:22,080
sutra transcription, and paranormal phenomenon.

133
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:26,090
We bought lots, since you want to find a hobby.

134
00:11:26,090 --> 00:11:30,460
- Thank you.
- Yakumo is considerate and capable at work.

135
00:11:30,460 --> 00:11:35,790
All the co-workers wonder why such a perfect guy is still single.

136
00:11:35,790 --> 00:11:38,070
- What are you saying?
- I'm telling her the truth.

137
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:40,870
<i>- Junko? I'm coming in.</i>
- All right.

138
00:11:42,510 --> 00:11:44,640
Yamashita?

139
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:46,620
You must've had a rough time.

140
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:51,250
Saki...?

141
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:58,830
W-What? W-Why are you here?

142
00:11:58,830 --> 00:12:00,110
With Yakumo?

143
00:12:00,110 --> 00:12:03,470
- He's a coworker at my part-time job!
- Part-time?

144
00:12:04,780 --> 00:12:09,650
What's your relationship with this man?  A dad-friend?

145
00:12:09,650 --> 00:12:11,890
T-This person is-

146
00:12:11,890 --> 00:12:15,750
I'm Harumi's old classmate. Matsuoka is-

147
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:19,050
- I'm Tanaka. Tanaka!
- What?

148
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:22,980
So...

149
00:12:24,630 --> 00:12:28,810
- Your coworker who proposed was... Yakumo?!
- Your old classmate who proposed was... Yakumo?!

150
00:12:28,810 --> 00:12:30,770
Propose?

151
00:12:32,090 --> 00:12:33,900
Yes.

152
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:41,200
So... Miwa is a divorcee who works at a company.

153
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:46,450
Nishioi is an unsuccessful dancer. Were you two lying to each other?

154
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:48,630
<i>- Yes.
- Yes.</i>

155
00:12:48,630 --> 00:12:51,700
- Why?
- I didn't want her to judge me based on education or job,

156
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:53,810
rather who I am as a person.

157
00:12:53,810 --> 00:12:55,600
Me too!

158
00:12:55,600 --> 00:13:00,590
You said money don't matter when I told you I was an unsuccessful dancer.

159
00:13:00,590 --> 00:13:02,080
That's because she has money.

160
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:03,220
Shut it!

161
00:13:03,220 --> 00:13:08,350
I've never imagined you being a successful owner, Saki.

162
00:13:08,350 --> 00:13:12,330
I've never thought you're an elite at a trading company that graduated from Harvard.

163
00:13:12,330 --> 00:13:15,080
- Oh, fabulous.
- Yes,

164
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,180
fabulous.

165
00:13:16,180 --> 00:13:19,630
I don't know what's going on here, but your childhood friend's highly skilled.

166
00:13:19,630 --> 00:13:22,230
Yeah, she's skilled alright.

167
00:13:22,230 --> 00:13:24,940
I heard you haven't contacted Yuri.

168
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:31,380
Don't worry. He said he gave it his all in the exams.

169
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:36,120
I'm so glad!

170
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:39,030
Tell him, "you did a good job".

171
00:13:39,030 --> 00:13:41,480
Tell him yourself.

172
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:50,380
Yakumo was the one who did a good job.

173
00:13:50,380 --> 00:13:54,160
He dashed out of the reception to the hospital, at the cost of a demotion.

174
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:55,860
- All for you, Junko.
- What?

175
00:13:55,860 --> 00:13:57,910
Nishioi, I told you not to tell her that.

176
00:13:57,910 --> 00:14:00,610
Is that true, Masashi?

177
00:14:01,420 --> 00:14:04,070
I'm sorry, all because of me...

178
00:14:04,070 --> 00:14:09,090
It's fine. I didn't want to go to Russia in the first place.

179
00:14:09,810 --> 00:14:14,940
Besides, I can bounce back in no time with my ability.

180
00:14:18,360 --> 00:14:20,430
<i>[Jonan General Hospital]</i>

181
00:14:20,430 --> 00:14:22,680
<i>[Sutra Transcription, The World of Paranormal Phenomenon, Fun Yoga Poses]</i>

182
00:14:27,770 --> 00:14:31,350
<i>- How was the reception?
- A success. A grand success at that.</i>

183
00:14:31,350 --> 00:14:34,280
<i> I thought you wouldn't wake up... </i>

184
00:14:35,990 --> 00:14:40,400
<i>The time you spend thinking of me, makes me very happy.</i>

185
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:43,150
<i>I love you. I've always loved you since I was little.</i>

186
00:14:43,150 --> 00:14:46,070
<i>And I love you even now. Marry me.</i>

187
00:14:53,020 --> 00:14:55,980
Come on. Sit down.
<i>[2018 Minami High School Graduation Ceremony]</i>

188
00:14:55,980 --> 00:14:57,690
Congrats on graduating.
<i>[Congratulations on Your Graduation]</i>

189
00:14:57,690 --> 00:15:00,460
Thanks!

190
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:01,890
This is our last class together.

191
00:15:01,890 --> 00:15:03,860
I'm sad, Yama-pyon.

192
00:15:03,860 --> 00:15:05,880
Yama-pyon, are you crying?

193
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:08,990
This is my last day as a teacher.

194
00:15:08,990 --> 00:15:13,490
This job leaves no immediate results,

195
00:15:13,490 --> 00:15:15,660
and you guys were idiots.

196
00:15:15,660 --> 00:15:21,050
I had my own struggles as a teacher. However, when you'll be as old as I am,

197
00:15:21,050 --> 00:15:23,320
I hope you'll have a good paying job,

198
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:27,490
and have one thing that makes you happy.

199
00:15:27,490 --> 00:15:29,730
I'd say I've accomplished my job.

200
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:33,770
Your life as adults, starts now.

201
00:15:34,710 --> 00:15:38,880
I wish you the best of luck. See you.

202
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:41,390
Look, Nara is crying.

203
00:15:41,390 --> 00:15:44,900
- I'm not crying!
- Yes, you are.

204
00:15:44,900 --> 00:15:45,700
Are you sad?

205
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:47,390
Stop it!

206
00:15:47,390 --> 00:15:48,890
Yuri.

207
00:15:51,350 --> 00:15:53,590
I visited Harumi at the hospital.

208
00:15:53,590 --> 00:15:55,770
How was she?

209
00:15:55,770 --> 00:15:57,820
She seemed to be doing well.

210
00:15:59,580 --> 00:16:02,340
She said you did a good job.

211
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:09,760
<i>Listen, it makes a cool sound.</i>

212
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:13,520
I want to try it, too. Let me try it.

213
00:16:13,520 --> 00:16:15,570
Kyo!

214
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:21,410
Since the exam results will be out tomorrow,

215
00:16:21,410 --> 00:16:24,330
I thought I might feel a little awkward.

216
00:16:25,030 --> 00:16:27,620
Eto, you'll pass.

217
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:30,550
I was able to push myself, thanks to you.

218
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:39,360
Kyo, I like you a lot.

219
00:16:41,550 --> 00:16:43,160
I'm sorry.

220
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:49,430
I thought so. I knew you find me annoying.

221
00:16:49,430 --> 00:16:53,380
Since Harumi-sensei is getting married, I thought I'd have a chance with you.

222
00:16:57,940 --> 00:17:02,140
Kyo, what will you do about Harumi-sensei?

223
00:17:02,940 --> 00:17:07,060
I'm no longer her student, so there's no issue.

224
00:17:07,670 --> 00:17:08,890
I'll do it in the right way.

225
00:17:08,890 --> 00:17:10,870
What do you mean by that?

226
00:17:12,410 --> 00:17:14,490
Once I pass,

227
00:17:15,140 --> 00:17:17,270
I'll tell her again...

228
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:20,030
that I love her.

229
00:17:20,030 --> 00:17:23,080
What is your plan after confessing?

230
00:17:23,080 --> 00:17:27,680
She is 34. Are you going to make her wait four more years?

231
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:30,810
More importantly, how will you provide for her?

232
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:40,840
I like both of you and Harumi-sensei.

233
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:43,760
I want the two of you to be happy.

234
00:17:46,050 --> 00:17:47,690
I'm sorry.

235
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,750
See you!

236
00:18:03,390 --> 00:18:05,140
I'll give you ride home.

237
00:18:07,690 --> 00:18:09,320
Thanks.

238
00:18:12,330 --> 00:18:14,670
- I heard you were getting discharged.
- Yes.

239
00:18:15,450 --> 00:18:17,120
Thank you.

240
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:19,400
It must be hard walking with this.

241
00:18:21,820 --> 00:18:27,080
I'm really sorry about... the job in Russia.

242
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:29,000
It's all in the past.

243
00:18:32,970 --> 00:18:35,950
No matter the circumstances,

244
00:18:36,740 --> 00:18:40,120
you've always been my ally, Masashi.

245
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:44,910
I made it this far because you were always there for me.

246
00:18:48,450 --> 00:18:54,240
Before the exams, you were studying diligently, just like I was.

247
00:18:56,950 --> 00:18:59,420
Masashi, you were the only one who understood me

248
00:19:00,650 --> 00:19:04,450
when I had issues with my mother.

249
00:19:04,450 --> 00:19:06,780
That was what saved me.

250
00:19:08,410 --> 00:19:11,570
Even when I failed my exams,

251
00:19:11,570 --> 00:19:14,210
failed to find a job,

252
